               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. CHAMBERS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">DOANE</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1449" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1449" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1449" type="surname" value="DYER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1449" type="given" value="CAROLINE"></interp>CAROLINE DYER</persName>
                  </hi>. My husband keeps a shop in Wellington-terrace, Spring-place, Wandsworth-road. On the 11th of Feb. the prisoner came for a 1/4lb. of sugar, he gave me a bad sixpence—I asked him where he got it from—he said his mother gave it him—I asked where his mother lived—he said, "Round there"—I said, "Round where?"—he said, in Frederick-place, South Lambeth, but he did not know the number—that her name was Brown—I sent Gastock to make inquiries—she came back, and said, in the prisoner's hearing, that she could not find any such person—I sent for the policeman—I gave the sixpence to my father.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1450" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1450" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1450" type="surname" value="MORGAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1450" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MORGAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I received the sixpence from my daughter—I held it in my hand till the policeman came, and I gave it him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-1451" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1451" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1451" type="surname" value="MENNIE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-1451" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MENNIE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 70.) I took the prisoner, and received this sixpence—I asked where he lived, he said, "Nowhere"—at the station I found on him this bad half-crown, wrapped in this bit of rag, and pinned inside the lining of his waistcoat—he made no remark.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
